article.headline: Iowa St. 71, Houston 67
article.story: HOUSTON -- Craig Brackins scored 38 points and had 14 rebounds to help Iowa State hold off Houston in a 71-67 victory Sunday. Diante Garrett added 12 points for the Cyclones (8-4), whose lead was cut to three on Kelvin Lewis' 3-pointer with 12 seconds remaining. Aubrey Coleman, who led Houston with 28 points, missed a 3-pointer with two seconds left that would have tied it. Kelvin Lewis added 15 points for Houston (7-2). Marcus Cousin had 11 rebounds and four blocked shots. Justin Hamilton had 12 rebounds for Iowa State. Houston led 27-26 at the half, but Brackins outscored Houston 5-0 to open the second half. The lead changed hands 11 times before the Cyclones took the lead for good with 9:58 to go in the second half on a 3-pointer by Lucca Staiger.
